caption: I got the breakfast bagel sandwich. It was simple and sloppy. The spinach was just thrown all in the middle. The tomatoes were not fresh. The cheddar looked like really cheap cheese. I ordered a salad as my side and it was literally just lettuce. So also cheap. I paid over $15 for pickup which was too expensive for what I got. I won’t be back :(

Came here on 3/5/21 with family and a friend that was here from California visiting. We were on the look out for Bruch with Mimosas around 9am. This place was a hit! The server provided great service. The Strawberry mimosas were delicious. We ended up buying 2 pitchers lol. I had the spicy feta cheese omelet and we shared the Kanela French toast. We wanted to try the red velvet French toast but the server mentioned they were out? (at 9am) which was odd. But nevertheless everything was made to perfection. Will need to come again!

The breakfast sandwich was absolutely delicious, just the right amount of spice. The only slight negative to the experience was that the waitress mixed our mimosas, I ordered grapefruit and my boyfriend ordered peach, but she didn't know which was which. Whichever one I had tasted great.
I called at 1pm and the person who answered said they close at 3pm but never did they care to mention last seating being at 1:45pm. Great communication skills.

(Translated by Google) Real, really delicious brunch restaurant. Most of all, the staff was really friendly! Red Velvet cake was so sweet and delicious 🥰❤️ The atmosphere was quiet and the coffee aroma was so subtle, so I think I enjoyed brunch more happily. The food is quite sweet and salty, but that's the charm of Canella〰️  (Original) 진짜 진짜 맛있는 브런치 레스토랑. 무엇보다 스태프가 정말 친절했다! 레드벨벳 케이크가 엄청 달고 맛있었음 🥰❤️ 분위기도 조용하고 커피향이 은은해서 더 즐겁게 브런치를 즐긴것같다. 음식이 꽤나 달고 짭짤하지만 그게 카넬라의 매력〰️
Great presentation and flavor. But highly disappointed in finding hair in the red velvet toast, not pleasing to be eating someone’s hair. As well as chicken not fully cooked

Food was amazing. Dine in was'nt an option but we were able to dine outside. They were able to bring an outside heater for us to maximize our atmosphere. Menu was unique and had a variety of healthy food options to choose from. Waitress was very friendly. Left there pretty satisfied. Would go back and I definitely recommend Kanela Breakfast Club
Great place for breakfast/ Brunch. Food selection is great and the portions are very generous.

If I can give zero stars I would. The service at this location was terrible. From the moment we walked in there, the server made us feel unwelcomed. He was giving every other table suggestions on what to order, except our table. Our food was sitting on the counter for a while and when I finally received my omelette and potatoes they were cold. I proceeded to tell the server about the food but he acted as if it was a bother for me to even speak to him. $50 for cold food and it was my grandmothers birthday. If you are not light skinned steer clear from this spot. (This is how certain staff here, in particular our server, made us feel).

There are many things to like about this place. The chicken and waffles are good but nothing like Chicago Chicken and Waffles, Peaches, and the litany of Black owned restaurants.  Still, good for what it is.  However, they lost stars for service. After multiple visits and attitudes from the wait staff, we no longer sit at the restaurant. The woman is always annoyed by something as simple as taking an order. Water refills don't happen. Acai bowls were basically purple soup that tasted like water with ice chunks. No bueno.  Fried egg sandwich is good, bacon is also delicious.
Impossible burger was a must

I had gotten the chicken and waffles and biscuits and gravy and they were wonderful! I would strongly recommend this place for breakfast food. The portions were very good as well. Still had plenty to save. If you’re not sure what to get try out the biscuits and gravy, can’t go wrong there!
Outstanding location for Breakfast. service is typically good. bring your appetite because portions are filling.

I ordered from ChowNow and one way or another, the order was mistakenly changed from delivery to pickup. Called the restaurant, they offered to get it delivered and then opted to remake my order since it had been sitting so long. Great staff, food is great and reasonably priced, I would order the entire menu if I could. Food is as good in person as the photos are!!

I have always wanted to come here & Boy it was Great! 🤗 The Food didn’t take long at all, Keep in mind they had one server and one cook. Food was Delicious, I definitely recommend going.
Decent food at a high price tag. Waitress was friendly.

Shout out to my waitress! She was literally incredible. I brought my dog to sit outside and she even brought us peanut butter to distract my hungry friend while we ate lol. I usually don’t write reviews but I really appreciated the help, warmth, and the excellent food. I was pretty hungover and I got a meal and one of their fresh pressed juices and I was back in action!! Will definitely be back
The food is very delicious and the service was very good. I had a good time!
Unbelievably good food! I loved the mimosa kit! Delivery was even quicker than expected! Great Sunday brunch!

The food was great (only reason I’m giving stars) but the service was honestly horrible. For starters the waitress (blonde girl) only checked up on us ONCE. for what we paid for I was seriously disappointed. She also did not bring my food all together and I was waiting for my bread for a long time. I actually had to ask her for it again. Now to pay our check we had to hunt her down because she would come no where near the our table. I came here because of the reviews but I’m seriously disappointed. FYI it wasn’t even that busy so I can’t imagine the service when it’s actually busy.

Tried this place for the first time and I was super satisfied with the meal and service. Everything was super food and our server was keeping the coffee flowing. Brunch burger was on point. Lox Bagel was massive and a great deal for the price

They have a nice variety of classic American food with a twist of flavors. We order fries, brussel sprouts, wings, and other finger foods. I just wish there were more in terms of quantity. I also tried their chicken and waffles and while it doesn't compare to South Carolina's Poogan's Porch, it surprisingly comes close! I went here for lunch last week. Not too busy. Waited about 10 minutes for someone to ask for our order or if we wanted a drink. I ordered a buttermilk chicken burger. Ate half of it, I had cut it in half, I thought wow this is juicy and moist. On to the second half I discovered the centre was raw. That's raw chicken! Of which I had already consumed a good deal of. Knocked it off of my bill, I still was charged for the cola I had drank. Not good enough. Service was a calamity, and to still charge for stuff after what could have been severe food poisoning? !
One of the best breakfast places in the west town/wicker park area! Their crab cakes are really good and so, is their strawberry orange juice. The servers are very friendly & accomodating.

Spectacular! After a 25 min wait on a Sunday at noon, I was ready to chow down on a breakfast burrito. The home made chorizo is very tasty and the flavor of the burrito as a whole was perfection! If you like some heat, ask for the salsa verde (green sauce). I’m a a bit of a sauce critic and this one is pretty damn good! The tomato soup was very flavorful and tasted as if cheese was baked right in! My mouth is watering just thinking about it! Service was good, restaurant was clean, food was spectacular! 5 stars all the way! Raved about it all week at work and I can’t wait to try something new!

Know the owners. Cool crop of men. Food is top quality, atmosphere is friendly and cultivating.  You'll get that much hungrier seeing other plates make it to their tables while you wait on your order.

Really good options for breakfast and brunch! The ambience is soothing and perfect for a good start of the day. Food is delicious and the serving amount is ample. It's a busy breakfast place and you can find yourself waiting in the line for your seats! But, If you have the liberty of time, it's worth the wait! They have good breakfast options and breaverages! Definitly recommended if you are staying nearby or just visiting nearby!👍

Not impressed.  Food was disappointing,  impossible burger was very dry, not very flavorful, the potatoes were dry/overcooked and lacked basic seasoning (salt), the monkey bread was dry/crumbly.  Coffee and service were fine... that's the only reason I gave them even 2 stars.
Long wait to be seated but....totally worth it!!! Fresh, savory....perfection. All the Ingredients are to each pair perfectly with each other and I will be here several times again.

Found this place on google and had heard of it through friends before so my best friend and I decided to give it a try. She ordered: eggs Benedict with side salad and matcha smoothie. My order: chilaquiles and berry blast smoothie. Our serve was very nice. There was no wait so we were sat quickly. Brought us a jug of room temperature water with two cups. No ice. To give the benefit of the doubt we could’ve asked for some. Anyways. Friend said smoothies were good which I agree they were delicious. She was satisfied with her dish. Now I couldn’t say the same. It was watery and had a funny taste to it. Now i understand a business is a business and we should pay for services of course. I conveyed to the server that I wasn’t too fond of the dish and if I could have an omelette instead and she responds nicely saying she can put the order in but just so I know that my original dish can not be taken off bill. I said ok. My omelette was delicious no problem. Our bill was $58.86 because they indeed did not remove the dish. I payed in cash $60 and the waiter returned and placed $3 exact on the table. Now I’m not cheap I tip very well at restaurants, having worked as a cashier and waitress many time before, though it was only 0.15 which I would could care less honestly I just think it’s the principle of the thing to bring back someone’s change or to at least ask if I could like the coins not just take it upon yourself and not give exact change back even after still charging me for a dish that wasn’t satisfactory. Needless to say I wouldn’t be back anytime soon. Perhaps will try one of their other locations.

Such a good brunch, we went two mornings in a row!  Wait isn't too bad in this area - only 20 mins on a Sunday at 11am.  Greek yogurt is amazing, maybe the best I've had outside Greece.

Super cute place. Good coffee and good food. Ask them to add the spicy feta cheese on your order. It's delicious.
Good breakfast options.

I've been here a few times and usually is during the week when it is not busy but I've visited also on the weekends and it can be very busy.  Either way the coffee is good (strong) and the food tastes good as well, and they offer vegetarian omelettes.  There is a small area to seat outside and  plenty of space inside,  I like that if they are busy, they can text you when a table is available.  Really enjoy the red velvet French toast and the Eggs Benedict. Will come back .
The food here is amazing and the bloody mary was also really good. I would highly recommend this place.
Excellent menu!!  Strawberry salad with chicken was delicious. Great location, as well.
Great service and equally good food! I’ll definitely give this place my business again!
We waited to get seated for 1 hour and then waited for our food for 1 hour and 10 minutes. They didn’t give us updates until we asked and nagged. food was ok. Definitely not coming back.
Red velvet french toast was great.  Opens early.  They have veggie sausage and veggie bacon which is a big plus.
Benedicts were great both times we went. Service was friendly and the vibe and music of the place were super cool.

I've had delivery here before, the food is fresh and healthy. I came in today and tried the breakfast burrito, It was amazing. I love the classic rock music and the ambiance of the restaurant. This is one of my favorite places to eat in my neighborhood.
Great food and a beautiful space. Try the French toast. It's lovely.
Amazing place. Great list of coffees and alcoholic drinks. Awesome menu to accommodate everyone with something to enjoy.

Food was delicious! Kanela roll and Mac to start. Biscuits and gravy and pork belly hash for entrees. La Colombe coffee and fresh juice! We had a very nice server (can't remember her name). She answered all my dumb questions quickly, accurately and honestly....without judgement and everything we asked for came out correctly. Not gonna lie...it was refreshing to have a server listen and do a good job. Only beef with this place is how many things I want to try. We will have to return on more than one occasion to work our way through their amazing selections. ❤

Excellent food and very friendly service. Creamy rich Mac and cheese, light crunchy cinnamon roll, great cappuccino and fresh juices, solid biscuits and gravy, unique savory and sweet pork belly Benedict. I can't wait to go back!

I've been wanting to try Kanela for ages, and I really wanted to like it since it's so close. We go there late on a Saturday morning, got seated reasonably quickly, and then it all went downhill from there. Service was so slow- took ages to get our menus, then to order. I'm pretty sure they forgot our food order, since we were waiting 20-30 minutes for all the dishes. There were other patrons who arrived after us, who got their food and ate and paid, all while we were still waiting for ours. Two out of the four dishes were incorrect- my friend's was missing the toast, and the fresh queso. Mine was the easiest dish, just mac and cheese, and it was the last thing to come out, after 30 minutes. It wasn't cooked through (the cheese was not melted on top), was missing the breadcrumbs, and clearly hadn't been baked as stated on the menu. The waitress apologized halfheartedly for the wait, but she barely checked in on us and never offered refills or anything, didn't even check how our food was once it finally arrived. I get if there's a rush in the kitchen or something, but this was bad service and bad food combined. To add insult to injury, not 30 minutes after eating (having eaten nothing else that day), I got sick. So not worth it.

If I had ordered my husbands meal the omelette with spicy feta OR my daughters meal which was a spicy benedict this would have been a 5 star review. I ordered the Lorraine scramble and it was meh..no cheese and very little onion or bacon and it made me sad. My other daughter ordered the hash and it had brussel sprouts as one of  the ingredients which was stated and which is loved by all of us but just didn't taste good in the hash. The la Columbe coffee is yummy but the latte even with an extra shot was pretty weak...I needed my caffeine! The waffle was nice and I think the girls french toast was too but didn't try it. Will go again for that spicy feta omelette for sure but not the Lorraine or the brussel sprout hash

Kanela breakfast club is amazing and great place. If you want eat a delicious brunch this places is for you.  Services is a really good, ask for Carmen she is very fast and patient with the tourist is a bilingual waitress.  100% recommended.

Update:  Raised to 4 stars as average of my two visits.  Second time: Built my own omlet, the spicy feta cheese is amazing, the homemade sausage is really excellent.  Service by Noah was spot on.  Everything came hot and fresh, this was the kanela club I was expecting.  First time visiting on a very uncrowded Friday morning.  Flavors were great, execution was lacking.  I had fried chicken and waffles, they sat in the window for 5 min before my wife's Benedict was ready.  Her poached eggs were so barely runny that it was sad.  To bad too, service was good, food tasted great, but they failed to bring it all together.  Wasn't worth sending back, just slightly disappointing for such an esteemed breakfast place.

She had a sleeveless, highly cropped top, which showed way more than I would like to see from someone serving food( talking about her chest and underarms).
